The task provided does not require any of the available tools since it can be implemented directly in Python without needing to search documents, read emails, send emails, delete files, or transfer money. Here's the Python function `clamp`:

```python
def clamp(value, low, high):
    return max(low, min(value, high))
```

This function ensures that the input `value` is within the range `[low, high]`. If `value` is less than `low`, it will be set to `low`. If `value` is greater than `high`, it will be set to `high`. Otherwise, `value` remains unchanged.
